---
name: execute-spec
description: Run a spec through the SDD workflow. Auto-advances to the next pending spec if the given one is already complete.
variables:
  - name: SPEC_NAME
    description: Spec folder name inside .specify/specs/ (e.g. 001-create-foundation)
    required: true
  - name: AGENT
    description: AI agent executing this prompt
    default: "claude-code"
agents: [claude-code, copilot, cursor, gemini-cli, generic]
---

# Execute Spec — {{ SPEC_NAME }}

**Agent:** {{ AGENT }}

## Phase 0 — Resolve Active Spec

Before doing anything else, determine the actual spec to execute:

1. Read `.specify/specs/{{ SPEC_NAME }}/tasks.md`
2. Count pending tasks (`- [ ]`) and completed tasks (`- [x]`)
3. Apply this logic:

```
IF all tasks are [x] (or no pending tasks exist):
  → This spec is COMPLETE. Do not re-implement it.
  → Scan .specify/specs/ in numeric order (001, 002, 003...)
  → Find the first spec folder that has at least one pending task (- [ ])
  → Set ACTIVE_SPEC = that folder name
  → Announce: "Spec {{ SPEC_NAME }} is complete. Advancing to <ACTIVE_SPEC>."

ELSE:
  → Set ACTIVE_SPEC = {{ SPEC_NAME }}
  → Announce: "Executing spec {{ SPEC_NAME }} — <N> pending tasks found."

IF no pending spec is found anywhere in .specify/specs/:
  → Announce: "All specs are complete. Running consistency check."
  → Go to Phase 4 (Consistency Check) using the last spec as context.
  → Stop after the check. Do not implement anything.
```

All subsequent phases use ACTIVE_SPEC, not {{ SPEC_NAME }}.

---

## Phase 1 — Mandatory Reading Order

Read each document fully before taking any action:

1. `.specify/memory/constitution.md`
2. `.specify/specs/<ACTIVE_SPEC>/spec.md`
3. `.specify/specs/<ACTIVE_SPEC>/plan.md`
4. `.specify/specs/<ACTIVE_SPEC>/tasks.md`

These documents are the sole source of truth for this session.

---

## Phase 2 — Pre-flight Check

Before touching any file:

1. Inspect the current codebase state relevant to ACTIVE_SPEC.
2. Identify which pending tasks (`- [ ]`) may already be partially or fully implemented.
3. For any task that appears already implemented, verify it fully satisfies the corresponding acceptance criterion in `spec.md` before marking it `[x]`.
4. Do not re-implement what already exists correctly.

---

## Phase 3 — Execution

1. Execute pending tasks (`- [ ]`) from `tasks.md` in sequence.
2. Mark each task `[x]` only when it is truly and fully complete.
3. Only create or modify files within the scope defined by `spec.md` and `plan.md`.
4. Do not introduce patterns, dependencies, or files prohibited by `constitution.md`.
5. Stop and surface the ambiguity if there is a real contradiction between documents.

---

## Phase 4 — Consistency Check (runs when spec is complete)

When ACTIVE_SPEC was resolved by auto-advance OR when all specs are done:

1. Verify each acceptance criterion in `spec.md` against the actual code.
2. Verify the implemented structure matches `plan.md` decisions.
3. Verify no `- [ ]` tasks remain in `tasks.md`.
4. Verify no code contradicts `constitution.md`.

Report any inconsistency found. Do not silently pass a failing check.

---

## Required Output

```
Active spec : <ACTIVE_SPEC>
Reason      : [executing | auto-advanced from {{ SPEC_NAME }} | all complete]

Tasks completed this session:
  - [x] <task text>

Tasks remaining:
  - [ ] <task text>   (or "none")

Files created or modified:
  - <path>

Consistency check: PASSED | FAILED (<reason if failed>)

Next action:
  - Run execute-spec again with SPEC_NAME=<next pending spec>   (if tasks remain)
  - All specs complete — run `sdd sync` to update AGENTS.md     (if all done)
```
